Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.62,0:00:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme selected \Nfor my comments this month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.55,0:00:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is “Punctuality—A Godly Quality.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.79,0:00:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You might remember the opening paragraph \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.59,0:00:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in a 1990 Watchtower article \Non the subject of punctuality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.53,0:00:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It said that an elder’s closest friends \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.54,0:00:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,jokingly called him Armageddon. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.27,0:00:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.57,0:00:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They replied: “We know he’s coming, \Nbut only God knows when!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.58,0:00:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The elder had a problem with punctuality.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.58,0:00:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Punctuality has nothing \Nin common with procrastination. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.19,0:00:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To procrastinate means \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.19,0:00:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“to intentionally put off \Nthe doing of something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.99,0:00:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that should be done.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.03,0:00:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The saying, \N“Tomorrow is the busiest day of the year” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.06,0:00:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,reflects the human tendency \Nto procrastinate.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.50,0:00:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How appropriate then \Nis the inspired encouragement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.30,0:00:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,concerning the present\N—today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.14,0:00:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Galatians 6:10 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.41,0:01:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“As long as we have the opportunity, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.75,0:01:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,let us work what is good toward all.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.88,0:01:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“As long as we have the opportunity” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.05,0:01:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,does not sound like procrastination to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.45,0:01:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the Bible encourages just the opposite\N—punctuality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.39,0:01:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Punctuality refers to the characteristic \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.13,0:01:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of being prompt in keeping appointments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.97,0:01:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Punctuality is a godly quality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.67,0:01:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Matthew 6:33 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.57,0:01:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,prioritizes our pursuit of Kingdom interests. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.21,0:01:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.58,0:01:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep on, then, seeking first \Nthe Kingdom and his righteousness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.85,0:01:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these other things \Nwill be added to you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.45,0:01:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It said to ‘seek the Kingdom first,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.29,0:01:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,not second, not third or fourth\N—first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.29,0:01:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When we put the Kingdom first in our life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.63,0:01:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we do not put it off \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.97,0:01:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in favor of some trivial pursuit.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.97,0:02:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is time for a Christian meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.54,0:02:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we are there well before it starts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.98,0:02:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you have heard some say: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.08,0:02:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“At least I made it to the meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.88,0:02:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Better late than never!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But the godly way is: \N“Better never late!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.69,0:02:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is a punctual God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.76,0:02:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He sets the example for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.06,0:02:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jehovah decided to destroy \Nthe ungodly world in a deluge, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.06,0:02:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,he said to Noah at Genesis 6:14: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.24,0:02:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Make for yourself an ark.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.37,0:02:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, at Genesis 7:4, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.37,0:02:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah told Noah \Nto enter into the ark and informed him: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.95,0:02:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“For in just seven days, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.71,0:02:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I will make it rain on the earth \Nfor 40 days and 40 nights.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.22,0:02:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.22,0:02:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A “better late than never” attitude? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that is not acceptable to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.23,0:03:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, Genesis 7:10 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.63,0:03:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“And seven days later \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the floodwaters came upon the earth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.40,0:03:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right on time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.40,0:03:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Punctuality is a godly quality.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,By means of a prophecy in Daniel chapter 9, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.35,0:03:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah indicated \Nhundreds of years in advance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.51,0:03:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jesus would fulfill \Nhis role as Messiah and Savior. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.89,0:03:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When did Jesus present \Nhimself for that role? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.19,0:03:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“Better late than never?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.26,0:03:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No, precisely on time in 29 C.E., \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was anointed as Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.10,0:03:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Romans 5:6 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.60,0:03:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“Christ died for ungodly men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.44,0:03:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at the appointed time.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.17,0:03:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is punctual.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.94,0:03:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What about in our time? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.95,0:03:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible tells us to keep in expectation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.45,0:03:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s future day of judgment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.22,0:03:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When will it happen? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.22,0:04:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to us it may seem that it has delayed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.13,0:04:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do we know about Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.83,0:04:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He is punctual. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.83,0:04:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it is that Habakkuk 2:3 tells us: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.70,0:04:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the vision \Nis yet for its appointed time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.21,0:04:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“and it is rushing toward its end, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.24,0:04:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“and it will not lie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.48,0:04:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“Even if it should delay, \Nkeep in expectation of it! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“For it will without fail come true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.92,0:04:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It will not be late!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.69,0:04:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Punctuality is Jehovah’s way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike the elder cited earlier, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.63,0:04:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,this Armageddon will be on time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.10,0:04:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul in 1 Corinthians chapter 14 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.67,0:04:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,was specifically discussing what happens \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.71,0:04:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at Christian gatherings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.77,0:04:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 26, he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.84,0:04:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“When you come together, . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.84,0:04:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let all things take place for building up.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.45,0:05:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, at 1 Corinthians 14:40, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,he concludes by saying: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.19,0:05:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“But let all things take place decently \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.06,0:05:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and by arrangement.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.43,0:05:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the words again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.89,0:05:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When speaking about Christian meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.93,0:05:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he said: \N‘Let things take place decently.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.63,0:05:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In Greek, \Nit literally means “well-behavedly.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.90,0:05:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul also used a Greek word \Ntranslated here “by arrangement.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.04,0:05:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The literal meaning of the Greek word \Nis “according to order.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If we are to be well-behaved, \Naccording to order at our meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.99,0:05:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what would be one aspect of that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Being punctual\N—on time—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.46,0:05:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for the start of the meeting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.46,0:05:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,While the lack of punctuality \Naffects all cultures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.10,0:05:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to one degree or another, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.17,0:05:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it is true that some cultures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.23,0:05:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are more punctual \Nthan others as a whole. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.84,0:05:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A missionary reported \Nthat in one town where he served, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.24,0:06:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,his wife would be \Nthe only person in the audience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.95,0:06:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,when he announced the opening song \Nat the beginning of the meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.45,0:06:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But when he announced the closing song, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.42,0:06:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,70 people would be there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, \Nin a Western European country, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.33,0:06:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,about a thousand people were asked: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you were invited \Nto dinner at 7:00 p.m., \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.37,0:06:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“should you arrive \Nfive or ten minutes early, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.37,0:06:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or five or ten minutes late, \Nor exactly on time?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.48,0:06:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The majority responded \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.48,0:06:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that “courtesy requires \Nscrupulous respect for the host \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.61,0:06:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and arriving at the exact minute.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.45,0:06:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Each culture would likely think \Nthat the other is extreme. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.32,0:06:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,However, being punctual is more \Nthan a matter of regional preference. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.43,0:06:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a godly quality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.50,0:06:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that true Christians of every culture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.63,0:06:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,want to cultivate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.64,0:07:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Punctuality must become a habit\N—a way of life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.71,0:07:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It is similar to some countries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.71,0:07:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that do not have \Na habit of good hygiene, or cleanliness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.21,0:07:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That may be true, \Nbut it is expected that Jehovah’s people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.59,0:07:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in those lands will excel \Nin good hygiene and clean habits. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.56,0:07:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In the same way, \Nno matter what our background, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.33,0:07:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,culture, or upbringing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.53,0:07:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it is expected \Nthat we as imitators of our God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,will develop \Nthe godly habit of being punctual.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.40,0:07:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What helps us to be punctual? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.11,0:07:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible encourages advance planning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.08,0:07:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 21:5 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.61,0:07:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“The plans of the diligent \Nsurely lead to success, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.62,0:07:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but all who are hasty \Nsurely head for poverty.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.46,0:07:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So being punctual is not just a matter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.06,0:07:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of hastily fulfilling \Nan obligation or an appointment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.96,0:08:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It involves thinking in advance \Nabout our responsibilities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.97,0:08:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, planning to be prepared for them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.60,0:08:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be prompt in carrying them out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.34,0:08:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what are some activities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.84,0:08:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that we would want \Nto be punctual in fulfilling? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.28,0:08:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be the everyday things in life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.65,0:08:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,such as arriving at work \Nor at school on time; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,being punctual for appointments, \Nsuch as a visit to the doctor or dentist; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.76,0:08:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,arriving at the designated time \Nwhen invited to another’s home for a meal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.50,0:08:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is our habit like \Nwhen it comes to these areas of life?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.91,0:08:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Even more important is punctuality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.08,0:08:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,when attending \Nour Christian meetings and assemblies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This means being present \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.58,0:08:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,before the opening song and prayer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.18,0:08:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul quoted from Psalm 22 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when he wrote Hebrews 2:12. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.76,0:09:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Of Jesus he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.29,0:09:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will declare your name to my brothers; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.13,0:09:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the midst of the congregation \NI will praise you with song.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.90,0:09:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If that was true of Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.70,0:09:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a great incentive \Nfor us to participate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.91,0:09:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in singing the first song \Nwith our congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.11,0:09:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And the opening prayer \Nis important for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.78,0:09:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In ancient times, \NJehovah called the temple \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.39,0:09:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,his “house of prayer.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.72,0:09:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true that the opening prayer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.96,0:09:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,requests Jehovah’s guidance \Nand holy spirit on the program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.43,0:09:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,however, it also prepares \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.10,0:09:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,our minds and hearts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to receive the information to be considered. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.54,0:09:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there may be times when one \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.77,0:09:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is unavoidably late in arriving at a meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.41,0:09:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Public transportation may be delayed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.98,0:10:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or our car may break down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.12,0:10:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s understandable on occasion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.82,0:10:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But what is our habit? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.26,0:10:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, \Nit was suggested that we consider \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.63,0:10:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,arriving 15 or 20 minutes \Nbefore a meeting started. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.66,0:10:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,One brother with six siblings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.20,0:10:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,said his father made a goal \Nof being at the Kingdom Hall \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.14,0:10:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,20 minutes before the program began. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.84,0:10:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That certainly took advance planning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.74,0:10:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,His father’s byline \Nfor meeting attendance was: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.55,0:10:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you’re 5 minutes early, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.58,0:10:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,then your 15 minutes late.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.75,0:10:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In most cases, the whole family arrived \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,20 minutes before the meeting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.93,0:10:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for wholesome association.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.83,0:10:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Another opportunity for punctuality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is arriving on time \Nfor a meeting for service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.44,0:10:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This is challenging for some. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.77,0:10:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,However, with a little advanced planning, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.78,0:11:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be successful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.81,0:11:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Punctuality is particularly important \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.45,0:11:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,since the actual meeting \Nis only about ten minutes long. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.39,0:11:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re late, \Nnot only is it disruptive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.22,0:11:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but it could force \Nthe one taking the lead \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.19,0:11:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to redo the arrangements \Nmade for the group. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.16,0:11:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And speaking of our ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.33,0:11:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,what is an opportunity \Nto be punctual every month? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you guessed it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.44,0:11:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,turning in our field service report \Nat the end of the month. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.74,0:11:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a way \Nof reminding yourself of this?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.25,0:11:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In some lands, \Nit is almost as if it is a custom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.68,0:11:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,for the start \Nof a wedding talk to be delayed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.12,0:11:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Often this is because \Nof mistakenly gauging how much time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.16,0:11:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the bride needs \Nto get dressed and made up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.93,0:11:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for her grand appearance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.77,0:12:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \Nbeing considerate of those invited \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.10,0:12:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,should move those involved \Nto allow extra time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.71,0:12:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to complete the task of preparation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.91,0:12:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A 1990 Watchtower \Ncommented on being punctual \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in starting a wedding. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The very next sentence stated: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.89,0:12:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“You may like to have your egg boiled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.99,0:12:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for just so many minutes.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.33,0:12:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not sure exactly how \Nthat applies to a wedding, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.50,0:12:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think we get the point, \Ndon’t we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.64,0:12:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We should have calculated \Nthe timing in advance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.57,0:12:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the ceremony begins on time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.48,0:12:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have yet another example \Nof being punctual, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,not procrastinating? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.95,0:12:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How about when there is a difference \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.62,0:12:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,between you and a fellow believer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.39,0:12:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or a family member? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.79,0:13:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, if it is simply a minor issue \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.23,0:13:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because of imperfection, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.23,0:13:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,often the best thing to do \Nis forgive and forget. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.84,0:13:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it was more serious \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.64,0:13:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or we cannot simply let it go, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.08,0:13:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what should we do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.18,0:13:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to settle the matter \Nand restore the peace. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.22,0:13:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When should we take this step? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not procrastinate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.12,0:13:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do, \Nthe problem may fester and get worse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.86,0:13:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of a priority \Ndid Jesus establish \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.00,0:13:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for restoring peace \Nbetween fellow believers? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.23,0:13:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At Matthew 5:23, 24, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.44,0:13:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,note his clear indication of punctuality: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.24,0:13:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“If, then, you are bringing \Nyour gift to the altar \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.18,0:13:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“and there you remember\Nthat your brother has something against you,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.02,0:13:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“leave your gift there in front \Nof the altar, and go away. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.19,0:14:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“First make your peace with your brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.29,0:14:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and then come back and offer your gift.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.83,0:14:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you pick up on the timing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.70,0:14:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus recommended for reconciliation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.90,0:14:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.90,0:14:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“[First] First make your peace \Nwith your brother.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.67,0:14:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a high priority \Nand should be treated as such. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.14,0:14:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember \Nthe scripture we shared earlier, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.58,0:14:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 21:5? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.82,0:14:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This principle should be implemented. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.12,0:14:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The last part of the verse \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.02,0:14:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,warns us not to be “hasty.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.13,0:14:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hasty is not synonymous with punctuality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.00,0:14:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, \Nthe first part of the verse indicates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.40,0:14:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we should prepare or plan the visit first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.31,0:14:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then follow through without procrastinating. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.94,0:14:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It said this approach will “lead to success.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.65,0:15:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the success we are seeking? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.12,0:15:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus did not say to justify our position \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.69,0:15:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or to point out the flaw \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.29,0:15:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in the other person’s words or actions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.70,0:15:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he said you would be successful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.97,0:15:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if you \N“make your peace with your brother.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.30,0:15:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Punctuality is a godly quality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.14,0:15:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that we should strive to cultivate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.51,0:15:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Another aspect of punctuality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.65,0:15:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is ending an assignment on time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.52,0:15:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In the interest of punctuality, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.72,0:15:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s move on \Nto the next segment of our program.\N
